FuncDef: The radius-server max-unresponsive-interval command configures the longest unresponsive interval for a RADIUS server. The undo radius-server max-unresponsive-interval command restores the default settings. By default, the longest unresponsive interval for a RADIUS server is 300 seconds.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the longest unresponsive interval for a RADIUS server.
The value is an integer that ranges from 10 to 7200, in seconds.
